f=AI & Agents/anneal/custom/prompt-context-engineering/SKILL.md · in=Ownership fleet agents structure their thinking context: internal prompt discipline, context priming, token economy, confidence disclosure. Tier-1 `prompting-practices` catalog entry finally owner shared skill's CONTENT maintained here; shared copy agent inherits lives Shared layer. · p=Prompting conventions drift per-agent unless one owner maintains shared discipline. Bad context habits (unstated assumptions, truncated work, unmarked confidence) fleet-wide failure modes, per-agent quirks. · wu=Maintaining/revising Shared prompting-practices skill (via normal Rail path)., lesson (self-annealing intake) traces thinking/context failure rather method failure., agent's skill needs prompt-shaped guidance reviewed (descriptions, trigger phrasing meta). · st:/ Protocol=shared discipline anneal maintains (current house rules, v2026-07): PRIME state knowns, assumptions, missing info before working; missing info requested `<FILL_IN>`-ed, never invented (rule 0.5). DELIMIT explicit separators between sub-tasks; one question escalation. NEVER TRUNCATE partial work surfaces `[INCOMPLETE: reason]`, never silently dropped. DISCLOSE CONFIDENCE recommendation ends `[CONFIDENCE: H/M/L basis]`; requires source formula (rule 0.6 alignment). TOKEN ECONOMY reference shared skills instead restating them; dated assets over inline stale facts. · in=Revisions shared discipline follow full annealing path: lesson baseline minimal diff proposal board apply Shared copy version., Reviews individual skills' prompt-shaped text (descriptions, trigger tables) apply meta's writing-skills SDO rules; findings route normal lifecycle intake., Fleet-wide prompt conventions never fork per-agent: agent needing exception gets documented conditional shared skill, local copy (local copies drift starts audit flags them). · of=Shared-skill revision proposals; per-skill review findings (rule-numbered, like meta's lint verdicts); maintained Shared